cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CY 

The paper focuses on privacy-preserving clustering in big data and IoT applications, which involves data management and privacy concerns. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a modified encoding mechanism that can be easily implemented in existing clustering algorithms, which relates to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CY (Computational Geometry).
